n on July 31. Safadi stated that the killing of Haniyeh was an attempt by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to 'expand the scope' of regional conflicts. Pezeshkian expressed hope that Jordan and Iran could improve diplomatic relations. US Central Command (CENTCOM) Commander General Michael Kurilla met with Israeli Chief of Staff Lieutenant General Herzi Halevi and Defense Minister Yoav Gallant on August 5 to finalize US-Israeli defense coordination ahead of Iran's and Iranian-backed groups' attack on Israel. Iranian-backed Iraqi militias likely conducted a rocket attack targeting US forces at Ain al Asad Airbase in Anbar Province, Iraq on August 5. The rocket attack reportedly injured several US personnel, according to three US officials speaking to Reuters. Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian announced three new appointments in his government on August 4. Pezeshkian announced the appointments of the following positions: Senior Adviser: Ali Taib Nia. Taib Nia served as former President Hassan Rouhani's economic affairs and finance minister between 2013 and 2017.
