**Iran and Axis of Resistance Plan Coordinated Attack on Israel**
Iran and the Axis of Resistance are planning a coordinated and large-scale attack on Israel in retaliation for the killing of several leaders of the Axis of Resistance, including the president of Hamas's political office, Ismail Haniyeh. According to US and Israeli officials, the attack is expected to occur as early as Monday. Iranian leaders have met with high-ranking officials of the Axis of Resistance, many of whom were already in Tehran for the inauguration of President Masoud Pezeshkian, to coordinate their combined attack. Some Iranian officials and state media have called for targeting Israeli political and military leaders in response to Haniyeh's death. For example, the president of the 'Martyrs and Veterans Affairs Foundation', Amir Hossein Ghazi Zadeh Hashemi, asked on August 1, 'to kill one of Israel's main leaders', a message echoed by IRGC-affiliated media that similarly stated that 'every Israeli political and military official is a potential target'. Iranian state media have also suggested that the next attack led by Iran against Israel will be similar but on a larger scale than the drone and missile attack launched against Israel in April 2024. Iran and the Axis of Resistance are considering how to inflict greater damage on Israel than the April 2024 attack, as that attack did not impose a significant cost on Israel and therefore failed to deter it. According to The Institute for the Study of War (ISW), 'Iranian leaders may increase the volume of projectiles fired against Israel, launching more from Iran, neighboring countries, or both. Hezbollah, the Huthi, and Iranian-backed militias in Iraq and Syria may launch simultaneous attacks to further test Israel's air defenses. Drones and missiles launched from Iraq, Lebanon, and Syria would be much harder to intercept than those from Iran, given the shorter distances and flight times to Israel. US and Israeli forces would have much less time to intercept those projectiles.' 
